summary:
Among commonly cited cytokines, only IL-8 exhibits robust chemotactic function by directing neutrophil migration into infected or injured tissues—a process central to initial containment of microbial threats. In contrast, while IL-1, IL-6, and TNF induce broader inflammatory reactions, these do not serve as potent recruiters of immune cells due to lacking clear directionality in leukocyte mobilization.

\boxed{C}

The summary above reflects both factual accuracy regarding biological mechanism and alignment with standard immunological teaching concerning functional distinctions between different types of cytokines involved in inflammation pathways.

